        <note appliesTo="source">line: 10</note>
      </notes>
      <segment state="initial">
        <source>Note: this add-on is not intended to be used in secure screens.</source>
        <target>Note: this add-on is not intended to be used in secure screens.</target>
      </segment>
    </unit>
    <unit id="2a0b6962-92f7-49b3-8090-9edf42048817">
      <notes>
        <note appliesTo="source">line: 11</note>
      </notes>
      <segment state="initial">
        <source>Nor is it able to support WASAPI at this time.</source>
        <target>Nor is it able to support WASAPI at this time.</target>
      </segment>
    </unit>
    <unit id="fae52030-2dbc-4570-a16f-b9f5da15e921">
      <notes>
        <note appliesTo="source">line: 12</note>
      </notes>
      <segment state="initial">
        <source>That means that it will disable itself in NVDA 2023.2 and above, if WASAPI is enabled in Advanced settings.</source>
        <target>That means that it will disable itself in NVDA 2023.2 and above, if WASAPI is enabled in Advanced settings.</target>
      </segment>
    </unit>
